      "side": 1,
      "message": "Correct. So the two choices that I see are:\n1. The input variable uses the child\u0027s mangle string, but is declared outside of the child\u0027s block. Being declared outside the block is really only a stylistic/semantics issue about where/when specific mangle strings are meaningful.\n\n2. The input variable must be created as format(\"%d_%s\", childIndex, parent\u0027s mangleString). This is probably very similar to what gets generated by #1, but makes it clearer that the parent scope is creating the variable. As you said, we\u0027d get problems if we left off the childIndex part of the name formatting.",
